cff-version: 1.2.0
message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: Multi‑path QUIC Performance Dataset with Energy and Traffic‑Shaping Measurements
abstract: This dataset captures the results of coordinated multi‑node experiments
  evaluating a QUIC implementation over dual‑path IPv6 topologies. Three hosts (client,
  proxy, server) were configured with deterministic traffic‑shaping, latency emulation,
  and configurable congestion‑control algorithms while transmitting predefined binary
  payloads. For each of ten iterations per configuration, the client, proxy, and server
  logged throughput, latency, QLOG traces, and process energy consumption. Post‑processing
  scripts generated visualisations, and all result directories were uploaded for archival,
  providing a comprehensive resource for reproducible network performance analysis.
